Then the non-probabilistic reliability index η can be obtained when the extreme value of the state function g(x1,…,xn) is available. X0=(xi0)n=(x10,x20,…,xn0) is the mean value or the nominal value of X=(x1,…,xn)T. The uncertainty of the structure δX can be regarded as the disturbance around the nominal value. Therefore, in the convex set theory, the uncertain vector X can be expressed as X=X0+δX, where X0=(xi0)n is the certain part, δX=(δxi)=xiU-xiL2 is the uncertain (disturbed) part denoting the uncertain degree or deviation. The uncertain deviation δX is assumed to change near the nominal value X0 in the following bounded convex set (i.e. hyper-ellipsoid), that is
(5)E(δX,θ)={δX:δXTΩδX≤θ2}
where Ω is an N × N dimensional positive definite real symmetric matrix called the weighting matrix, θ is a positive number called the radius of the hyper-ellipsoid. The shape and size of the hyper-ellipsoid is determined by the weighted matrix Ω and the radius θ.
